sagwara"},{"html":"<b>Madam Speaker:</b> It has been moved by the honour�able\nmember for Union Station, seconded by the honourable member for St. Johns, that\nBill 201, The Restricting Mandatory Overtime for Nurses Act (Various Acts\nAmended), be now read a first time. ","index":"00012","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>MLA Asagwara:</b> I'm proud to present to the House Bill 201, The\nRestricting Mandatory Overtime for Nurses Act.","index":"00013","speaker":"Uzoma Asagwara"},{"html":"����� Prior to the\npandemic, our health-care system struggled due to lack of capacity exacerbated\nby the&nbsp;government's unwillingness to address nursing vacan�cies. Sadly,\nCOVID-19 has only exposed and increased challenges where these gaps exist.","index":"00014","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Staffing\nvacancies have led to employers relying on mandating overtime to levels that\nput both the employee and patient safety at risk. Bill 201 will end the\npractice of using mandatory overtime to fill vacan�cies and vacation and allow\nnurses the right to refuse overtime and not be in breach of their duty of care.\n","index":"00015","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Thank\nyou. ","index":"00016","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Is it the pleasure of the House to adopt the motion? <i>[Agreed]</i>\n","index":"00017","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> The honourable Minister of Families�and I would indicate that the\nrequired 90&nbsp;minutes notice prior to routine proceedings was provided in\naccordance with our rule 26(2). ","index":"00018","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Would\nthe honourable minister please proceed with her statement. ","index":"00019","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><span lang=\"FR-CA\">Hon. Rochelle </span></b><b><a name=\"_Toc67039979\"><span lang=\"FR-CA\">Squires</span></a></b><b><span lang=\"FR-CA\">�(Minister responsible for Francophone Affairs):</span></b><span lang=\"FR-CA\"> Madame la pr�sidente, il me fait un grand plaisir de prendre la\nparole aujourd'hui